I think recent discussions about the “body positive” movement essentially saying it is making people want to be fat is so tired. God forbid a woman is allowed to live in the world without her value being measured and judged by glancing at her waistline. One person might look at me and think I look healthy and another might look at me and think I’m promoting an unhealthy lifestyle. Wherever you are at in your journey, it’s okay to simply honor your body where it’s at right in this moment and realize your entire existence doesn’t have to be centered about your size.
You don’t have to love your body all the time but you also don’t have to hate it 🤍

I give you your @boden_clothing denim guide! #ad 
 
High Rise 90s Tapered Jeans | Go for these if you are looking for that classic denim look and feel. These are more rigid but still have a little bit of stretch which helps them keep their shape. I wear the size 32.
 
Mid Rise Slouch Wide Leg Jean | If you’re looking for a baggier more relaxed jean you’ll love these. They are 100% cotton so they don’t have much stretch. I wear the size 32. 
 
High Rise True Straight Jeans | If you like your jeans ultra high rise with a lot of stretch, these are for you! These run bigger than the other pairs so size down. I wear the size 31.

From the creator of the coastal cowgirl aesthetic herself, here is your coastal cowgirl starter pack. If you want to hear @kristinazias and I give our full Spring/Summer 2023 trend breakdown tune in to the latest episode of the @confidentcollective podcast!

After 2 years, The Bikini Breakdown is making a comeback! 

Growing up I would say no to pool parties, avoid days at the beach, and just feel such a sense of dread if I knew I had to be in a swimsuit. That is why I am so passionate about helping you find swimsuits that you love and make you feel GOOD. Your body should never hold you back from doing anything. 

So get ready for a new Bikini Breakdown video every Wednesday! I want your fine ass to be strutting your stuff in a bikini all summer long!! #bikinibreakdown

Spend a morning with me in NYC featuring the new drop earrings from @lightboxjewelry. They make incredible lab-grown diamonds which actually have the same chemical properties as a natural diamond. They’re accessibly priced and I love that these earrings add some major sparkle for daily wear. #LightboxJewelry
Honestly pissed that no one stopped me to ask where my outfit was from…

Long story short… I spent too much money this weekend.

My girl @lovefashionfriends and I wanted to show you the @loft high-rise slim flare jeans on 2 different body types. I am a size 14 and Dileiny is a size 2 and we both look hot if I do say so myself. #ad

I always thought my life would be so much better if I was thinner (I hate to admit that sometimes I still feel a thought like this creep in). I felt this so intensely that is stopped me from wearing certain things or even doing things that I wanted to do because the hatred I felt for my body ran so deep. 

I specially remember the absolute dread I felt when I knew I had to be in a swimsuit. I think that is why I am so passionate about sharing swimwear and helping you find a swimsuit that you feel good in. 

So here is a little teaser for the first Bikini Breakdown of 2023! You don’t have to wait to lose weight to wear the swimsuit! 

This shoot with @sydney_sweeney with @frankiesbikinis was ICONIC so I had to recreate it to show you that curvy girls can do it too.

The Bikini Breakdown | Frankies Bikinis 

If you are looking for a sexy yet cute teeny weeny little bikini @frankiesbikinis is the spot! This is where you can find super unique design that you can’t find anywhere else. I am wearing a size XL in all of these suits and you can find links to everything in my bio under “shop my looks” 👙 ☀️

The Bikini Breakdown | Victoria’s Secret

Do you remember when @victoriassecret was THE place to shop for swimsuits? I do too and back then I didn’t really feel like I had options that would work for me. I think for the price they have created some beautiful swimsuits that will give you lots of support! 

I typically wear a 36DDD in VS bras but in the swim I need to size down to the 36DD tops and XL bottoms. All of these suits come in tons of colors and different bottom styles so you can have as little or as much coverage as you’d like. 

I think these suits are a great option at a bit of a lower price point and I love that you are able to mix and match top and bottom styles as well as colors and prints.

The Bikini Breakdown | Cuup Swim 

This one is for my girls with big boobs! @cuup goes up to a 42H. I am wearing The Balconette Top with the Bikini Bottom and The Scoop One Piece. 

I think the top is incredible but I really do not like the bikini bottoms. I think having compression swim in low rise is tricky becasue it can dig into you. I think the high waist bottoms might be the better option.

I do however, love the one piece! I like compression in a one piece but not so much in a two piece! I think this is so beautiful and you feel snatched and supported. #bikinibreakdown #cuupswim #midsizeswim #swimreview #cuupswim

Have you purchased your ticket for the @confidentcollective pool party yet?? We are saying “fuck that” to needing to change your body before summer or needing to lose weight before putting on a swimsuit. 

We want you to come and celebrate your body exactly where it is now. So come party with us in LA on June 17th! You can get your ticket through the link in my bio! 

If you already have a ticket, here is a little outfit inspo for you for what to wear! The most important thing is to wear what makes you feel sexy AF. 

Drop a 👙 in the comments if you’re coming!!

The Bikini Breakdown | Good American 

I’ve got to say, I think @goodamerican is the only brand making swimsuits that are cute and actually size inclusive. The carry styles in XXS - 5XL. They also have options that are skimpy and more modest.

I tried @goodamerican’s Compression swim as well as their Always Fits Bikini. One of my favorite one piece swimsuits is from GA, so I am not surprised I liked these suits. If you’re looking for a one-piece that sucks you in and has cup support I do think the suit I showed from Cuup last week fits better in the bust but I like the colors and cut of the Good American suit slightly better! 

The Always Fits fabric reminds me of the fabric of Youswim. My only complaint on this one is that the waistband does not have much give! I think the tie front top is ADORABLE! 

If you are looking for a more full coverage bikini I think the last one is perfect! I love the sporty look and the color adds some playfulness while the cut is still modest.

Compression One Piece - XL
Always Fits Top -  L
Always Fits Bottom - L/XL
Compression Top - XL
Compression Brief - XL

I’ll be totally real with you, my self talk have been shit lately because I’ve been feeling like shit about myself. I am not sure where this is coming from but I had to remind myself how sad of an existence it is to be constantly thinking about how others view your body. Or thinking your only value lies in how you look. Beauty is subjective and I can choose to hate on myslef or embrace myself for where I am at right now. So here is to embracing our goddess energy.

Finding pieces of clothing that make you feel confident is the best feeling. @abercrombie has been killing the game. I am obsessed with their skorts! You get the look of a mini skirt but are so much more comfortable. #AbercrombiePartner Use TIKTOKAF for 20% off now through 7/24

I always say I feel like my best self in the summer time. It might be the sun on my skin or the salt water in my hair but I feel so much more at home in my body. All of the excess is stripped away and I feel like I can appreciate my natural beauty. Bare Rose by @victoriassecret is the perfect summer fragrance, with notes of rosa centifolia and pear skin. It is fresh and crisp. It does not cover you it is an extension of you, letting your best self shine through.

Who remembers how big of a deal the Victoria’s Secret holiday catalogs used to be?? I recreated a few looks from a 1993 @victoriassecret catalog and imagine if the catalogs featured curve models back then? I wonder how different a lot of us would feel about ourselves growing up. I have seen some criticism online of people saying the angels were supposed to be unobtainable that’s why everyone was so fascinated by them, but that instills such a narrow view of beauty. This idea of what is beautiful was created and handed to us. We all deserve to feel glamours and sexy.
